Harvard Lectures w/ David Malan.

Javascript Lecture:

-- Fast and good Javascript is necessary for clients. Don't add unnecessary features!
-- Compiles line by line and not precompiled.
-- Javascript Server Side -- Node.js.
-- Let's say you want to focus on a username field. What would the code look like? This is an example used:
<script>
    // put cursor in username field if empty
    if (document.forms.login.username.value === '')
    {
      document.forms.login.username.focus();
    }
    // else putcursor in password field
    else 
    {
      document.forms.login.password.focus();
    }
</script>

-- on.submit="return validate();" is an example of the usefuleness of JS it is validating the info before it reaches the server.
Script Example: 
<script>
    if (document.forms.registration.email.value == "")
    {
        alert("Need Email")
        return false;
    }
    else if (etc..)
    {
    etc..
    }
return true;
</script>
 

